r the first time, we observe\ndirect, experimental signatures of Fermi arcs in Mo$_x$W$_{1-x}$Te$_2$, which\nagree well with theoretical calculations of the surface states. However, we\ncaution that the interpretation of these features depends sensitively on free\nparameters in the surface state calculation. We comment on the prospect of\nconclusively demonstrating a Weyl semimetal in Mo$_x$W$_{1-x}$Te$_2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Dec 2015 20:20:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-31"}
