cal{B}\\subseteq{[n]\\choose s}$\nis ${m-t\\choose r-t}{n-t\\choose s-t}$ for $\\min\\{m,n\\}\\geq n_0(r,s,t)$, where\n$n_0(r,s,t)$ is close to best possible. We obtain analogous results for\nfamilies of integer sequences and for families of multisets. The results yield\ngeneralisations for $k\\geq2$ cross-$t$-intersecting families, and\nErdos-Ko-Rado-type results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Dec 2015 20:36:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-31"}
