t}, and $F=\\sum_{j=0}^n\nK_j(\\cdot- y_j) = K_0 + \\sum_{j=1}^n K_j(\\cdot-y_j)$. Also an emphasis is put\non relaxing all other technical assumptions and give alternative, rather\nminimal variants of the set of conditions on the kernel.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Dec 2015 22:22:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Feb 2016 22:12:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 17 Apr 2016 18:06:57 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 15 Aug 2017 06:02:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-17"}
